properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 11 at 4:07AM EST until January 12 at 10:00AM EST by NWS State College PA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest to west winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts around
45 mph expected.

* WHERE...Montour, Northumberland, Columbia, Dauphin,
Schuylkill, Lebanon, Adams, York and Lancaster Counties.

* WHEN...From 2 AM to 10 AM EST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The strongest wind gusts will likely occur
around and shortly after the time of a strong cold frontal
passage prior to daybreak.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

For high wind safety information, visit weather.gov/wind.

The latest forecast information can be found on the
NWS State College Facebook page and Twitter @NWSStateCollege,
or on the web at weather.gov/ctp.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 2 AM TO 10 AM EST SUNDAY
